  "market_context": "After a failed first attempt where 5-minute up-close candles formed equal highs without a higher time frame level, the analyst reframed the setup using the hourly chart, identifying buy side liquidity above and an hourly fair value gap as the relevant higher time frame PD array.",
  "key_observation": "A valid order block requires a higher time frame point of interest. Pairing an hourly fair value gap with a 5-minute sweep and closure over the down-close candle produces a valid bullish order block entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the hourly ETH chart, identify buy side liquidity resting above and an hourly fair value gap as the important HTF level.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 5-minute chart and wait for price to reach into the hourly fair value gap.",
    "Step 3: Confirm a liquidity sweep occurs once price taps into the fair value gap.",
    "Step 4: Wait for a closure above the opening price of the down-close candle that swept liquidity, validating it as a bullish order block.",
    "Step 5: Place a limit entry at the order block's opening price on the retest, with stop on the low and target set at 2R (buy side liquidity).",
    "Step 6: Trade reaches the 2R take profit target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit the 2R take profit target successfully.",
  "lessons": "An order block is only valid when it forms at a higher time frame point of interest. Without HTF confluence such as an hourly fair value gap, the same 5-minute pattern is just equal highs in a retracement and will fail.",
